messages:
Name: Mustapha Yatabaré
Nationality: Mali
Date of Birth: January 26, 1986
Position: Attacker
Current club: Sivasspor
Süper Lig clubs played for: Trabzonspor, Kardemir Karabükspor, Konyaspor, Sivasspor

Sivasspor's Mustapha Yatabaré has taken part in the vast majority of the club's Süper Lig matches in 2020/2021, making 31 appearances overall and playing 2,230 minutes. He has started in 27 of these appearances across their 40 fixtures and been used as a substitute on four occasions.

The last Süper Lig match that Yatabaré played came on May 15 for Sivasspor against Kasımpaşa; a match that he played just one minute in during a 2-1 success. In total, he has scored 10 Süper Lig goals this term, making him the team's second-top league scorer, and provided two assists. He has been booked six times.
It was against Konyaspor on April 11 when Yatabaré last scored, netting in a 3-1 win. His opening goal of the campaign came in the 3-1 victory against Kayserispor on October 17.
In last season's Süper Lig, Yatabaré featured in 31 games for Sivasspor, scored 13 goals and provided four assists.
Before joining Sivasspor in July 2019, Yatabaré made 34 league appearances in total at Konyaspor, scoring five goals and providing three assists.
